text: Today I had the pleasure of announcing more candidates who will hold the banner of the @peoplespca in Manitoba. J’ai eu le plaisir d’annoncer aujourd’hui d’autres candidats qui porteront l’étendard du @ppopulaireca au Manitoba.pic.twitter.com/5KGh1Iclo1
Our styles may be occasionally different. Our goals are not. We need Warren to help fight the good fight. #ClimateCrisis

Warren and I both care a lot about better government and a better Canada. And I’m happy to have a fighter helping us achieve that. We are united in devoting our lives to political discussion to achieve better governance and improved lives for Canadians.
Great turnout in Guelph. In response to a question about @KinsellaWarren I said some past campaigns had been despicable ⁠— not Warren, but what our politics has too often become.

Serving up lunch in Petawawa with @jensstoltenberg – a small way to say thank you to the women and men of the @CanadianForces who bravely stand up and serve for Canadians & our @NATO allies. You protect our most fundamental values, and we will keep supporting you & your families.pic.twitter.com/PaDJ2t1zEN

Je sers le dîner avec @jensstoltenberg à Petawawa pour remercier les femmes et les hommes de @ForcesCanada qui servent courageusement les Canadiens et nos alliés de @NATO. Vous protégez nos valeurs les plus fondamentales, et on continuera de vous soutenir ainsi que vos familles.pic.twitter.com/xZkTtPXlJ4

As a founding member, Canada plays a key role in @NATO. Today, we focused on Canada’s commitment to the alliance and our leadership in advancing peace & security, including our contributions in Latvia, Iraq, & Ukraine, and efforts to increase the number of women military leaders.pic.twitter.com/uYyg7U5XXR

#NATO was built on a very Canadian ideal: we’re stronger together. The alliance can count on Canada – we've always worked side by side to protect our citizens and everyone who dreams of a brighter tomorrow. Thanks to @jensstoltenberg for the productive meeting in Petawawa today.pic.twitter.com/6SB5sr59GB

Le Canada joue un rôle clé dans @NATO. On a parlé de l'engagement du Canada envers l'Alliance, de notre leadership dans la promotion de la paix et de la sécurité, notamment en Lettonie, en Irak et en Ukraine, et de nos efforts pour accroître le nombre de femmes chefs militaires.pic.twitter.com/swj95DdDsR

L' #OTAN incarne un idéal très canadien: l’union fait la force. L'Alliance peut compter sur le Canada. On a toujours travaillé côte à côte pour protéger nos citoyens & ceux qui rêvent d'un avenir meilleur. Merci à @jensstoltenberg pour la réunion productive à Petawawa aujourd'hui.pic.twitter.com/2v72EM8kmH
